<p>April. 1916.</p>
<p>Apr.1st.<br/>"Fools day"- no jokes or false alarms- Football &amp; Boxing under Capt. Brownell- lecture by Capt. Hamilton- "Veneral Diseases"- Continued bombardment on British front- Half- holiday (?).<br/>Apr. 2nd.<br/>Sabbath- Mass 9 a. m. - Pleasure walk- Issue of two gas respirators- Salmons. Sauce.  Pears &amp; Lime juice. No! not issued-  Letter-writing- "R.C faith in France."</p>
